## Hard test rules

- **RLS NULL-coalescence rule.** Every RLS `USING` and `WITH CHECK` clause must coalesce role-check results (e.g., `coalesce(public.get_user_role(), '')`). A bare `public.get_user_role() = 'manager'` evaluates to NULL when the function returns NULL, and Postgres treats `NULL = anything` as NULL — which the policy may accept depending on the operator. The convention guard regex must match the function name in *every* OR-branch of the clause, not just somewhere in the clause text. See handbook `patterns/web/rls-null-coalescence-guard.md`.
- **Proxy-on-mutation-target rule.** Atomicity tests must throw from inside the database client, not from the function-call boundary. A throw at the call boundary doesn’t engage the rollback path because no mutation has happened yet. Use a Proxy that intercepts the actual mutation method (e.g., `from(...).update(...)` rather than the action wrapper). See handbook `patterns/test-correctness/proxy-on-mutation-target.md`.
- **Deliberate-violation verification.** Any institutional-memory test (security guard, atomicity, regression spy) must be exercised by deliberately reverting the fix and confirming the test fails for the right reason. Document the deliberate-violation log in the commit message of the session that adds the test. See [`decisions/examples/deliberate-violation-verification.md`](https://github.com/rajivjc/engineering-handbook/blob/main/decisions/examples/deliberate-violation-verification.md).
- **Atomic state via Postgres RPC.** Multi-row mutations live inside a Postgres function. Server actions call the RPC and treat the result as success or complete failure. No application-level multi-step mutations, no try/catch-then-cleanup application logic. See [`principles/atomic-state.md`](https://github.com/rajivjc/engineering-handbook/blob/main/principles/atomic-state.md).
- **Single source of truth for projected values.** When a value flows to multiple surfaces (PDF, CSV, UI, JSON API), it is computed once in a transformer function and consumed by every surface. See [`principles/single-source-of-truth.md`](https://github.com/rajivjc/engineering-handbook/blob/main/principles/single-source-of-truth.md).

